    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of the Nisqually, a Native American people who once dominated the Snoqualmie River area in west-central Washington. Today the Nisqually retain a reservation on the Snoqualmie River near Tacoma, Washington.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
